title: Syria’s south rocked by protests amid anger over fuel hikes
description: In the city of Sweida, rare demonstrations followed the government’s decision to cut fuel subsidies, a blow to people already dealing with hyperinflation and poverty.

title: Before Prigozhin plane crash, Russia was preparing for life after Wagner
description: After Prigozhin’s presumed death, the Kremlin, internal Wagner factions and outside paramilitary forces are jockeying for control of a lucrative global empire.

title: U.S.-Iran prisoner deal highlights plight of other foreign detainees
description: A potential U.S.-Iran prisoner swap that could free four Americans is bringing attention to others with Western passports who remain imprisoned in Iran.

title: British Museum director resigns over handling of thefts
description: Gold coins, necklaces and pottery are among the hundreds of artefacts missing from the British Museum since 2013.

title: Kremlin dismisses as ‘lies’ speculation linking it to Prigozhin death
description: The Kremlin spokesman ridiculed theories in the West that the crash was an assassination ordered by Putin — however among Russia’s elite, there is little doubt Putin was behind it.

title: As China’s economy slows, the buck stops with leader Xi Jinping
description: Xi could come under political pressure as the economy falters. While there are no obvious challengers to his leadership, there are signs of passive resistance.

title: Before child died in custody, CBP tried to replace medical contractor
description: U.S. Customs and Border Protection sought to replace Loyal Source Government Services, LLC, the medical contractor that operated the ward where a girl died in May.

title: Trump-admiring libertarian’s surprise primary win upends Argentina
description: In the days after congressman Javier Milei’s victory, the government devalued the peso by 22 percent and looters ransacked supermarkets. Economists now forecast inflation to increase 175 percent this year.

title: Ukraine live briefing: Putin appears to eulogize Prigozhin; Pentagon says Wagner chief’s death ‘likely’
description: In his first remarks since the plane crash, Russian President Vladimir Putin said Wagner chief Yevgeniy Prigozhin was “talented” but “made serious mistakes.”

title: Russian plane crash debris points away from accident, experts say
description: Aviation experts agreed that the available evidence thus far points away from a simple mechanical problem or human error.

title: Prigozhin’s presumed death casts fate of Wagner’s operations in doubt
description: The main question remaining for the mercenary group: Which remnants of its once-sprawling empire will Russian President Vladimir Putin take over?
